com.ge.predix.mobile.core

Class MobileManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ge.predix.mobile.core.MobileManager

  • @Singleton
public final class MobileManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Copyright Â© 2016 GE. All rights reserved.
    The MobileManager is the core of the Predix Mobile SDK system. It is the component used to bind your platform user interface to the internals of the SDK. Your container is responsible for providing a window or view where authentication, is loaded, and a separate window or view to load the PM web app into. The manager can be used to register custom services prior to startup. It can also be used to obtain the core component responsible for distributing notifications.

    • Method Detail

      • getState

        public MobileManager.PMMState getState()
        This method is used to obtain the current state of the mobile manager. The manager can be in one of the following states: IDLE indicates no activity is happening. INITIALIZING indicates the mobile manager is in the process of initializing and creating internal objects. It should not be interacted with during this state. STARTED indicates the manager is completely started and ready for further method invocations. STOPPING indicates it is in the process of shutting down and deallocating internal components.
        Returns:
        MobileManager.PMMState object representing the current operating status of the MobileManager.

      • getServiceRouter

        public ServiceRouter getServiceRouter()
        Use this method to obtain an instance of the ServiceRouter which can be used to register additional Predix Mobile services. A Predix Mobile Service is a Java object that responds to an http://pmapi RESTful call. These objects are decorated with RequestMapping annotations that dictate which objects and methodsrespond to which RESTful calls.
        Returns:
        an instance of the ServiceRouter

      • instance

        public static MobileManager instance()
        Factory method used to obtain an instance of the Predix mobile manager. The mobile manager is the object used to bind the SDK to your application.
        Returns:
        an instance of the Predix Mobile manager.

      • setViewInterface

        public void setViewInterface(ViewInterface viewInterface)
        The ViewInterface is an abstraction around the component used to link Predix Mobile SDK behaviors to your application. It contains methods that allow you to bind an AuthHandler component, a WindowView component, the platform's context and a system preferences component.
        Parameters:
        viewInterface - Set your container's implementation of the ViewInterface

      • wipeDeviceData

        public void wipeDeviceData(WipeDeviceDataCallback callback)
        Called to wipe all of the device's data for secure purposes. The supplied WipeDeviceDataCallback is invoked upon completion.
        Parameters:
        callback - A WipeDeviceDataCallback which receives a call upon completion.

      • start

        public void start()
           throws InitializationException
        This method starts the mobile manager and invokes the equivalent of a http://pmapi/boot/start REST command. Configuration is read in from the preferences and config files. The internal service router is instantiated and all core and custom services will be registered.
        Throws:
        InitializationException - Thrown if start is called when the manager is in the middle of stopping.

      • getNotificationSender

        public NotificationSender getNotificationSender()
        Used to return an instance of the component responsible for distributing platform notifications. Use this component if you wish to send custom notifications which can be delivered to JavaScript web code that can register for the notification.
        Returns:
        a NotificationSender that distributes system and/or custom notifications.

      • getNotificationRegistrar

        public NotificationRegistrar getNotificationRegistrar()
        Used to return an instance of the component responsible for registering for platform notifications. Use the object returned by this method if you wish to subscribe an object for notifications. The subscribing object must have at least one Subscribe annotation.
        Returns:
        An instance of the NotificationRegistrar used to subscribe objects for notifications.

      • stop

        public void stop()
          throws InitializationException
        Called to shut down the mobile manager. At the conclusion of this method, all registered services are stopped, unregistered and shut down. The SDK stops listening to notifications, and cancels all network reachability updates. It finally returns to an IDLE state.
        Throws:
        InitializationException - thrown if stop is called while the manager is in the middle of starting up.
